{
  "text": "The networks of the subtype-specific feature genes reveal the hub components representing each of these IHC-defined subtypes. NOTCH1, a key component present in [ER+ |PR+ ]HER2\u2212 tumors, symbolizes the importance of Notch signaling in such cancers, which is an evolutionarily conserved mechanism that mediates communications between cells [CITATION_1] . CDKN2A could induce cell cycle arrest in G1 and G2 phases [CITATION_2] , whose presence in [ER+ |PR+ ]HER2+ tumors suggests the representative roles of cell cycle signaling on tumors of this subtype.",
